//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_yoke}

NOTE: This operation writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»` into every vessel's {rbrv_regime} file under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}` so that subsequent Cloud Build operations (conjure, bind, graft, enshrine) consume the named tool image set as GCB step images.
The about/vouch pipeline (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft) consumes reliquary tool images uniformly across all ordain modes; bind additionally uses skopeo for image-copy.
The stamp is validated once against GAR before any vessel file is touched: all six tool packages must be present under the reliquary subtree.
On stamp validation failure the operation errors diagnostically without writing any vessel.
On per-vessel write failure the diagnostic identifies the failing vessel and the set of vessels already written, so the operator can resume from a known point.
This primitive does not commit; the caller (orchestrator or operator) commits the {rbrv_regime} changes.

The
{rbtr_director}
yokes a reliquary stamp across every vessel:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtr_director}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«STAMP»` provided as first positional argument (e.g., `r260327172456`)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *List Reliquary Packages in GAR*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[packages.list] for
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
/
{rbrd_gcp_region}
/
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
with `pageSize=1000`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Filter response package names to those starting with `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/`
.. Strip the subtree prefix to yield the bare tool-name set present in GAR

//axhos_step
. *Verify Tool Image Completeness*:
.. Expected tool name set: `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `skopeo` (per
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe})
.. {rbbc_require}
all six names present in the filtered list
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if any expected tool is missing — the error message names `«STAMP»`, the reliquary subtree path, and the specific missing tool(s); remediation points at
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

//axhos_step
. *Iterate Vessels under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`*:
.. Enumerate every immediate subdirectory of `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}` containing an {rbrv_regime} file
.. {rbbc_require}
at least one vessel found — empty enumeration is a fatal error (nothing to yoke)
.. For each enumerated vessel, perform *Rewrite the {rbrv_regime}* below in directory order
.. Maintain a running list of vessels successfully written; emit per-vessel progress

//axhos_step
. *Rewrite the {rbrv_regime}* (per vessel):
.. Load the vessel's {rbrv_regime} file into memory, line by line
.. For each line matching `^RBRV_RELIQUARY=` — substitute with `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»`, preserving position
.. All other lines pass through unchanged
.. If no `RBRV_RELIQUARY=` line was found — append one under a `# Tool Image Reliquary` comment header
.. Write the composed content to a per-vessel temp file, then atomically replace the {rbrv_regime} file via rename
.. {rbbc_fatal}
on any per-vessel I/O failure — the error message names the failing vessel and the list of vessels already written, so the operator can resume from a known point

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»` into the {rbrv_regime} file of every vessel discovered under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`; no GAR state is modified.
The primitive does not commit — the caller (orchestrator or operator) commits the modified {rbrv_regime} files with their usual git workflow.
The reliquary tool images are now linked, but vessel images must be rebuilt
({rbtgo_ark_ordain})
to pick up the new tool versions.

include::RBSDI-depot_inscribe.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_yoke]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_yoke}

Yokes a reliquary stamp across every vessel's
{rbrv_regime}:
validates the stamp once against GAR, then rewrites `RBRV_RELIQUARY` in every {rbrv_regime} file under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDY-director_yoke.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_delete]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_delete}

Jettisons a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.

include::RBSIJ-image_jettison.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_retrieve]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_retrieve}

Wrests a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
{rbtr_director}-tier — peer to {rbtgo_image_delete}, distinct from {rbtgo_ark_summon}.

include::RBSIW-image_wrest.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_rekon]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_rekon}

Reports canonical-member presence under a hallmark or reliquary subtree in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_image}).
Two distinct procedures (`rbfl_rekon_hallmark`, `rbfl_rekon_reliquary`); rekon-on-enshrinement is intentionally omitted (enshrinements are 1-deep).

include::RBSIR-image_rekon.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_audit]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_audit}

Lists identifiers under one of three GAR domains (hallmarks, reliquaries, enshrinements) in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_image}).
{rbtr_director}-tier flat catalog; complements the {rbtr_retriever}-tier {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}, which adds health classification on the hallmark domain only.

include::RBSIA-image_audit.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_abjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_abjure}

Formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from the repository
({rbtgog_ark}),
removing its image, about, and vouch artifacts as a coherent unit.

include::RBSAA-ark_abjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_ordain]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_ordain}

Ordains a hallmark from a vessel — the master ceremony dispatch operation.
Detects vessel mode (conjure, bind, or graft) and delegates to the appropriate
{rbtga_ark}
creation path, then chains metadata and vouch pipeline stages.

[[rbtgo_ark_conjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_conjure}

Conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
by building a container image
({rbtgog_ark})
from a vessel specification.
Build context delivered via {rbtga_ark_pouch}, submitted via `builds.create` API. The combined job produces both the `image` and `about` packages under the hallmark subtree (about steps embedded via stitch). Vouch is a separate Cloud Build job using DSSE envelope signature verification.

include::RBSAC-ark_conjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_enshrine]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

Enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing content-addressed
{rbrv_image_anchor}
references from
{rbrv_image_origin}
declarations.
The
{rbtr_director}
submits a Cloud Build job that copies each upstream image by tag to GAR with a human-readable anchor tag, and writes the anchor back to the vessel regime.

include::RBSAE-ark_enshrine.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_graft]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_graft}

Grafts a locally-built container image into the
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark})
via native docker/podman push.
The image push itself is local (no Cloud Build); about and vouch follow as Cloud Build jobs.

include::RBSAG-ark_graft.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_kludge]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_kludge}

== Axial Key Premise Terms

[[axk_premise]]
{axk_premise}::
A
{axl_motif}
representing a declared design constraint or assumption that explicitly bounds system complexity.
Premises eliminate classes of problems by stating what the system will not handle, simplifying design.

== Infrastructure Terms

[[axo_dependency]]
{axo_dependency}::
A
{axl_motif}
representing required component or library for operation.
Specifies external requirements for functionality.

== Compliance Rules

This section specifies compositional requirements between motifs.
When a term voices a particular motif, these rules define what companion elements are required.

=== Operation Detail-Site Completeness

A term voiced
{axvo_procedure}
or
{axvo_method}
with a detail-site subdocument requires:

* {axhob_operation}
— opens the hierarchy block, with lookahead to the operation's linked term

* At least one
{axhos_step}
— what the operation does

* {axhoc_completion}
— how the operation signals success or failure

Optional markers that MAY be included:

* {axhopt_typed_parameter}
/{axhopa_arg_parameter}
/{axhopm_motif_parameter}
— input parameters (typed/arg variants use 1-arity lookahead; motif is bare)

* {axhoot_typed_output}
/{axhoom_motif_output}
— produced artifacts (typed variant uses 1-arity lookahead; motif is bare)

* {axhoq_precondition}
— environmental state requirements before execution

* {axhog_guarantee}
— environmental state guarantees after success

=== CLI Subcommand Completeness

Voicing as
{axi_cli_subcommand}
requires:

* Exit Status section voiced as
{axa_exit_uniform}
or
{axa_exit_enumerated}
(which voice
{axhoc_completion}
in CLI context)

* Arguments section voiced as
{axa_argument_list}
(which voices
{axhopt_typed_parameter}
/{axhopa_arg_parameter}
in CLI context; may list zero arguments if operation takes none)

=== CLI Option Completeness

Voicing as
{axa_cli_option}
requires the definition text to specify:

* Long form (e.g., `--file`)

* Short form or explicit absence (e.g., `-f` or "none")

* Default value, if the argument is used with
{axd_defaulted}

=== Argument List Item Qualification

Within an
{axa_argument_list},
each item requires a preceding
{axd_dimension}
annotation specifying at minimum:

* {axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* {axd_defaulted}
if a default value applies

=== Type Voicing Qualification

Voicing a type (subspecializing
{axt_*}
or
{axtu_*}
motifs) constrains dimension usage.

Valid dimensions:

* {axd_list}
— type intrinsically represents delimited collection

Invalid dimensions:

* {axd_required},
{axd_optional},
{axd_defaulted}
— presence applies to usage sites, not type definitions

* {axd_repeated}
— repetition applies to usage sites, not type definitions

=== Regime Specification Completeness

Voicing as
{axrg_regime}
requires:

* Format dimension (
{axf_bash},
{axf_makefile},
{axf_json},
etc.) specifying how assignments are carried

* Provenance dimension (
{axrd_file_sourced},
{axrd_env_inherited},
or
{axrd_constructed})
declaring how
{axrg_assignment_s}
arrive

=== Regime Variable Qualification

Voicing as
{axrg_variable}
requires:

* Type in annotation (base type motif or type voicing)

* At minimum
{axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* {axd_defaulted}
if a default value applies

Valid dimensions:

* {axd_required}
— variable must have assignment

* {axd_optional}
— variable may be absent

* {axd_defaulted}
— fallback value when absent

* {axd_list}
— inherited from type voicing; variable's type is a delimited collection

Invalid dimensions:

* {axd_repeated}
— regime files use unique keys; multiple assignments of same variable not permitted

* {axd_nullable}
— format-dependent;
{axf_bash}
has no null distinct from empty string

=== Regime Voicing Annotation Completeness

{axvr_regime}
requires:

* {axf_format}
dimension specifying how
{axrg_assignment_s}
are carried

{axvr_variable}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the parent regime

* {axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* Type
{axl_motif}
(base type or type voicing)

{axvr_group}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the parent regime

=== Regime Hierarchy Consistency

* {axvr_group}
with
{axd_conditional}
requires corresponding
{axhrgb_group}
in subdocument to have at least one
{axhrgc_gate}

* {axvr_group}
without
{axd_conditional}:
corresponding
{axhrgb_group}
must have no
{axhrgc_gate}

* Every
{axvr_variable}
under a regime should appear as either
{axhrv_variable}
or
{axhrgv_variable}
in the subdocument

=== Operation Voicing Annotation Completeness

{axvo_procedure}
requires:

* Exactly one lifecycle dimension:
{axd_transient},
{axd_longrunning},
or
{axd_periodic}

* If
{axd_grouped}:
second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be an
{axo_group}

{axvo_method}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the affiliated
{axo_entity}

* Exactly one lifecycle dimension:
{axd_transient},
{axd_longrunning},
or
{axd_periodic}

* If
{axd_grouped}:
third
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be an
{axo_group}

{axvo_group}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the affiliated
{axo_entity}

* Optional exposure dimension:
{axd_tabtarget},
{axd_slash_command},
or other interface mechanism specifying the default exposure for external members

=== Operation Hierarchy Consistency

* {axhob_operation}
attribute reference must match a term voiced
{axvo_procedure},
{axvo_method},
or
{axvo_tabtarget}
at the
{axl_definition_site}

* Every
{axhoc_completion},
{axhopt_typed_parameter},
{axhopa_arg_parameter},
{axhopm_motif_parameter},
{axhoot_typed_output},
{axhoom_motif_output},
{axhoq_precondition},
{axhog_guarantee},
and
{axhos_step}
must appear within
{axhob_operation}
scope

